<DOC><DOCNO> AP890126-0123 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-26-89 1355EST</FILEID><FIRST>d a AM-BRF--Bakker-Trial     01-26 0138</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Bakker-Trial,0142</SECOND><HEAD>Bakker, Dortch Ask For Delay of Trial</HEAD><DATELINE>CHARLOTTE N.C. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Attorneys for former PTL leaders Jim Bakkerand Richard Dortch have filed motions seeking to have their clients'trial postponed from next month's federal court session.   In motions filed Wednesday in U.S. District Court in Charlotte,the attorneys said they needed more time to prepare their case.   Bakker, who resigned as PTL president in March 1987 following asex and money scandal, and Dortch, Bakker's top deputy at PTL, wereindicted Dec. 5 following a 16-month federal grand juryinvestigation. The indictment accuses them of diverting more than $4million in PTL funds for their personal use.   Each was charged with 24 counts of mail fraud, wire fraud andconspiracy to commit mail and wire fraud. Both have pleaded notguilty to the charges.</TEXT></DOC>